<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/10346028-marlee"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1461115725i/10346028._UY100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/10346028-marlee">Marlee</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I personally find the book much better than the movie. If the book never existed, I would say the movie was beautiful on its own, but the book leaves <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I personally find the book much better than the movie. If the book never existed, I would say the movie was beautiful on its own, but the book leaves it in the dust. A lot more story and characters, much more humor, and very easy to get lost in. <br />Overall, if you're more of an art and animation fan, the movie is the way to go. If you want more story, the book.<br />Not to mention there are two books that follow it that are also high up on my favorites list.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
